section.section:
On receipt of the criminal history record information of a licensee forwarded to the Board in accordance with § 8-303 of this subtitle, in determining whether to renew a license, the Board shall consider:
The age at which the crime was committed;
The circumstances surrounding the crime;
The length of time that has passed since the crime;
Subsequent work history;
Employment and character references; and
Other evidence that demonstrates whether the licensee poses a threat to the public health or safety.
